   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON FIFTEEN THE SENSE OF THE SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND KNOWING THE SPIRIT 2 Scripture Reading: Romans 8:2, 6 OUTLINE previous chapter Consciousness: Of life: The higher the life, the richer being its consciousness.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The divine life being the highest life with the richest consciousness.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>This life within us causing us to be full of spiritual consciousness, enabling us to sense the spirit and the things of the spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Of the law of life: The law of a conscious life belonging to the realm of consciousness.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The law of the Spirit of life being full of consciousness.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Of peace: The peace within us being entirely a matter of consciousness.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The consciousness of peace enabling us to know that we are in the spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Of death: Death causing us to lose consciousness.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Death also causing us to have the sense of death.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Knowing the spirit by the sense of the spirit: By the sense of life: The divine life being contained in the Holy Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The Holy Spirit mingling Himself with our spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The divine life becoming the life of the Holy Spirit and of our spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>This divine life in the Holy Spirit through our spirit giving us the senses of life.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>By such a sense of life we know the spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>By the sense of the law of life: The law of life being the natural function of the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The functioning of the law of life.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The law of life giving us the natural sense on the positive side and the unnatural sense on the negative side.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The natural sense versus the unnatural sense of the law of life.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>By the sense of peace: The life of the Holy Spirit in our spirit being God Himself.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Our spirit with the divine life contained in the Holy Spirit being the new man.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>God as our life versus our self.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The new man versus our old man.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The sense of peace being the issue of walking and living by the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>By such a sense of peace we know that we are living in the spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>By the sense of death: Death being the issue of our flesh, including our old man.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Death being the opposite of both life and peace.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The negative senses of death.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>By such negative senses, we know that we are not in the spirit.</S>
   </TEXT>
